HEADWORD: leadplant
<hw>leadplant</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shrub (<spn>Amorpha
canescens</spn>) of sandy woodlands and streambanks of the Western U. S.
having hoary pinnate flowers and dull-colored racemose flowers; it is
thought to indicate the presence of lead ore.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lead plant, <spn>Amorpha canescens</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

